cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.AI, cs.MM 

The paper proposes a new type of convolutional layer for convolutional neural networks (CNNs) that is motivated by local binary patterns (LBP). Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also focuses on the efficiency of the proposed layer, which suggests that it could be relevant to categories such as cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Additionally, the paper discusses the theoretical and experimental performance of the proposed layer, which could make it relevant to categories such as cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.MM (Multimedia).
